        high: 'Mixed states involve simultaneous activation of sympathetic and ventral vagal branches. The high energy of sympathetic activation is contained within the social engagement system\'s neuroception of safety. This produces play, performance, athletic competition, sexual intimacy with a safe partner, and the productive intensity of “flow.” Porges identifies play as a critical practice for building vagal tone and resilience.'
