      scenario: 'Imposter Syndrome (High School)',
      icon: '\uD83C\uDFAD',
      forBand: 'high',
      forZone: 'yellow',
      summary: 'For the constant feeling that you do not belong in the room \u2014 the AP class, the team, the program, the friend group. Even when the evidence says you do.',
      triggers: ['Getting accepted somewhere prestigious', 'Being the only one who looks like you in a space', 'A peer who seems naturally great', 'Compliments that feel hollow', 'Realizing how much you do not know yet'],
      earlyWarning: ['"They are going to figure out I do not belong"', 'Over-preparing, over-working', 'Refusing opportunities you actually want', 'Discounting your accomplishments', 'Comparing your inside to others\' outsides'],
      strategies: ['Name it: "This is imposter syndrome. Most high-achievers feel it."', 'Collect evidence of your actual work \u2014 files, grades, projects', 'Ask a trusted mentor: "Do you actually think I belong here?"', 'Distinguish: discomfort with being new vs. actually being unqualified', 'Mentor someone slightly behind you \u2014 it shows you how much you do know', 'Talk to peers \u2014 chances are they feel it too', 'Reframe: "I do not know that yet" (growth) vs. "I am stupid" (fixed)', 'Read about imposter syndrome \u2014 almost every successful person has had it'],
